<tr>
    <td class="text-nowrap">3.1.1 Language of Page</td>
    <td>A</td>
    <td>
        Both assistive technologies and conventional user agents can render text more accurately 
        when the language of the Web page is identified. Screen readers can load the correct pronunciation rules. 
        Visual browsers can display characters and scripts correctly. Media players can show captions correctly. 
        As a result, users with disabilities will be better able to understand the content.
        <br>
        <strong>It helps: Visually impaired, cognitive impaired</strong><br>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/language-of-page.html" target="_blank">
            WCAG: Understanding 3.1.1: Language of Page
        </a>
    </td>
    <td>
        Use the lang attribute for the HTML element.
        <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes/lang" target="_blank">MDN: lang attributes format (parts)</a>
    </td>
</tr>
